  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Deluxe Double Rooms</strong> are around 26m² and have a king size bed, sleeping two people with space for a cot. Rooms with south-facing balcony and glacier view are available for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Superior Double Rooms</strong> are around 26m² and have a king size bed. They sleep two to three people (extra bed is a double sofa bed that can sleep a child aged 14 and under). Rooms with south-facing balcony and glacier view are available for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Junior Suites</strong> are around 35m² and sleep two to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed). These rooms are available on request, please call us to book.</p>
<p><strong>Suites</strong> offer the most space at around 50m². They sleep two to four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed) and are available on request, please call us to book.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Balcony</li>
<li>Seating area</li>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Fridge</li>
<li>Tea &amp; coffee making facilities</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Bath or shower</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>3pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. CHF7.00 per person per night is payable locally. Children aged 6-15 years pay a discounted rate of approx. CHF3.50 per night, and children aged 5 and under are exempt.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Steps into property: <strong>No</strong></li>
<li>Adapted rooms: <strong>Yes</strong></li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
